dwm - dynamic window manager
============================
dwm is an extremely fast, small, and dynamic window manager for X.


Requirements
------------
In order to build dwm you need the Xlib header files.


Installation
------------
Edit config.mk to match your local setup (dwm is installed into
the /usr/local namespace by default).

Afterwards enter the following command to build and install dwm (if
necessary as root):

    make clean install


Running dwm
-----------
Add the following line to your .xinitrc to start dwm using startx:

    exec dwm

In order to connect dwm to a specific display, make sure that
the DISPLAY environment variable is set correctly, e.g.:

    DISPLAY=foo.bar:1 exec dwm

(This will start dwm on display :1 of the host foo.bar.)

In order to display status info in the bar, you can do something
like this in your .xinitrc:

    while xsetroot -name "`date` `uptime | sed 's/.*,//'`"
    do
    	sleep 1
    done &
    exec dwm


Configuration
-------------
The configuration of dwm is done by creating a custom config.h
and (re)compiling the source code.


Keyboard bindings
-----------------

M-p             Dmenu
M-Shift-Return  terminal
M-j             cycle windows
M-k             cycle windows
M-i             increment master
M-d             decrement master
M-h             decrement master size
M-l             increment master size
M-Shift-x       kill client
M-Return        zoom
M-Tab           swap view back and forth
M-Shift-c       kill client
M-t             set layout 0
M-f             set layout 1
M-m             set layout 2 (maximized)
M-Space         set layout (cycle?)
M-Shift-Space   toggle floating
M-1..9          switch view
M-0             all views
M-Shift-0..9    tag client to view (0 will tag for all views!)
M-period        focus monitor (decrement)
M-comma         focus monitor (increment)
M-Shift-period  tag client to monitor (decrement)
M-Shift-comma   tag client to monitor (increment)
M-Shift-q       quit
M-Ctrl-0..9     toggle view
M-Ctrl-Shift-0..9 toggle tag


Mouse bindings
--------------

Left-click tagbar:   show clients with tag.
Left-M-click tagbar: swap client tag.
Right-click tagbar:  add clients with tag.
Right-M-click:       add tag to client.
Left-M window:       float & move
Middle-M window:     float
Right-M window:      float & resize
